      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:21:4",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) أَكْثَرَ مَا يَجْلِسُ تُجَاهَ الْقِبْلَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from one of his companions, fromTalha Bin Zayd, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘It was so that Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> used to mostly sit facing the Qiblah’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from certain individuals of his people from Talhah ibn Zayd from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah most of the time would sit facing the direction of Qiblah (Ka’bah).” "
        ]
      }
    }
